org.apache.ctakes.utils.xcas_comparison

Class XcasDiff

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ctakes.utils.xcas_comparison.XcasDiff

  • public class XcasDiff
extends Object
    An XcasDiff object represents the comparison results of two XCAS files. It also provides methods to output these results.
    Author:
    Mayo Clinic

    • Method Detail

      • recalculate

        public final void recalculate()
        Calculates the differences or recalculates after the two files are updated. Works on an copy of the original annotations. Original objects are not touched. Must be called if the original XcasFile is modified elsewhere.

      • printDiff

        public static void printDiff(XcasFile f1,
                             XcasFile f2)
        Prints elements that are unique to each XCAS file to stdout. First constructs an anonymous XcasDiff object, and calls its printDiff(). Avoid using this method if you plan to use XcasDiff object later.
        Parameters:
        f1 - An XcasFile object.
        f2 - Another XcasFile object.
        See Also:
        printDiff()

      • printHTML

        public static void printHTML(XcasFile f1,
                             XcasFile f2,
                             Writer w)
        Writes an HTML summary of the comparison of the two specified XCAS files. First constructs an anonymous XcasDiff object, and calls its printHTML(Writer). Avoid using this method if you plan to use XcasDiff object later.
        Parameters:
        f1 - An XcasFile object.
        f2 - Another XcasFile object.
        w - An Writer object to write to.
